	(text_box "Crystal: \n- Abracon ABM3-8.000MHZ-B4Y-TNominal Frequency 8.000 MHz\n- Rated Load Capacitance C_L 18 pF\n- Max Equivalent Series Resistance (ESR): 140 Ohm\n\nPCB Stackup & Geometry Assumptions:\nBased on the JLCPCB 8-layer stackup (JLC08161H-1164) and the designed layout:\n- Trace Width: 0.15 mm\n- Total Trace Length l: 8.5 mm (combined OSC_IN and OSC_OUT)\n- Primary Dielectric: PrePreg (epsilon_r ~ 4.2)\n- Ground Plane Strategy: Void/Cutout on L2;  L3 used as the reference ground plane. \n- Distance to Reference Plane h: 0.1164 { mm (D1)} + 0.0152 { mm (L2)} + 0.3 { mm (D2)} = 0.4316 mm\n\nTrace Capacitance:\nUsing the IPC-2141A empirical approximation for microstrip self-capacitance:\n- C_trace ~ (0.0264 * epsilon_r + 0.0129)/ln(5.98 * h/0.8 * w) [pF/mm]\n- epsilon_r = 4.2 (dielectric contant)\n- h = 0.4316mm (height to L3)\n- w = 0.15mm (trace width)\n\nC_trace ~ ((0.0264 * 4.2) + 0.0129)/ln(5.98 * 0.4316/0.8*0.15) ~ 0.0403 pF/mm\n\nTrace lenght total (from osc_in and out down to crystal pins) ~ 7.5mm -> 0.30pF\n\nTotal Stray Capacitance:\n- C_s = C_trace + C_MCU_pin + C_crystal_pad + C_parasitic_margin\n- C_MCU_Pin - 4.5pF (Internal STM32G4 input/output capacitance) - from datasheet\n- C_crystal_pad: 0.2pF (5031 SMD pad capacitance to L3 ground) - parallel-plate capacitance of the large SMD pads of the 5032 package agains L3 (0.4316mm)\n- C_parasitic_margin: 0.96pF (Safety margin for vias and manufacturing tolerances)\n\nTotal C_s ~ 6.0pF\n\nExternal Load Capacitor\n- To satisfy the crystal's required CL, we solve for CL1 = CL2 -> C_ext = 2x(CL - C_s)\n- C_ext = 2 x (18pF - 6.0pF) = 24pF\n\nStandard E12 value: 22pF, COG/NPO\nEnsuer copper keep-out (void) on Layer 2 direcetly beneath the crystal and oscillator traces to maintain the calculated height h.\n\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 20.32 16.51 0)
		(size 43.18 34.29)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.5 0.5)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "5e8f6304-8994-490f-8984-b34e3b0e62ab")
	)
	(text_box "TODO: Second Low Pass Filter and current limiter for pin protection\n\nSampling Time: When Betaflight initializes the ADC on an STM32F405, \nit hardcodes the sampling time for the VBAT (battery voltage) channel to 480 cycles (ADC_SampleTime_480Cycles).\nThis is the slowest and most stable sampling time available on the STM32. \nIt's done for one specific reason: to give the ADC's internal capacitor plenty of time to charge, \nwhich is required when reading from a high-impedance source (like your divider).\nImpedance Required: This 480-cycle sampling time is what allows the ADC to work with a source impedance up to the datasheet's maximum of 50kΩ."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at -68.58 97.79 0)
		(size 59.944 36.322)
		(margins 1.3525 1.3525 1.3525 1.3525)
		(stroke
			(width 0.8)
			(type solid)
			(color 255 0 0 1)
		)
		(fill
